    "body": "broken URLs found by algolia docsearch.\r\n\r\ntodo:\r\n\r\ndocsearch is picking up these URLs, maybe `gendoc.lua` has a bug?: cc @yochem \r\n\r\n    https://neovim.io/doc/build/install/\r\n    https://neovim.io/doc/install/build/",
    "closed_at": "2026-02-24T11:56:50Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Thanks. I've curl'd all `href`'s that point to a non-https url (but including https://neovim.io) and checked their status:\r\n\r\n\r\n- `000 ./build/`: docgen bug\r\n- `000 ./build/#build-prerequisites`: idem\r\n- `000 ./install/#install-from-source`: idem\r\n- `301 /doc/user`: works on GH pages but probably better to fix anyway\r\n- `404 /doc/user/netrw/#netrw`: found a [comment in gen_help_html.lua](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/gen/gen_help_html.lua#L1144) that says netrw doesn't work in CI\r\n- `404 /doc/user/netrw/#netrw-browse`: idem\r\n- `404 /doc/user/netrw/#netrw-quickmap`: idem\r\n- `404 /node-client/`: isn't served locally so not a bug\r\n\r\n",
